76561197998177676,Recommended,318570,14528396,"Posted: 18 February, 2015",all,Hassat Hunter,"Hunters of the Dead is a game specifically build around organisation of your team. Actions like resting, healing and training are all necessary, but keeps your Hunters from fighting. To win you carefully need to balance between which to keep present for combat, and which you can savely miss a few turns.While the first few games you're bound to loose to find that sweet spot, you gain gold which you can use to gain permanent upgrades to your game-start, making things easier aswell.Turns (or days) progress by capturing buildings, each one serving serving a different function to reinforce your team.Inevitably, you'll find opponents in these structures and combat starts. Combat follows the ""Plants vs. Zombies"" lane principles, where the Hunters you can put to action depend on which you didn't send off for healing/training or are too fatigued (no Action Points) to fight. While the amount of units and opponents is limited, the primary difficuly from these sections does not stem from what to use against what foe as in PvZ, but more what units did you have available, and are you capable to deal with the loss of Action Points and Health in preperation for the next fight."
