,Not Recommended,318570,15165141,"Posted: 1 April, 2015",all,The Semp,"I want to like Hunters of the Dead a lot. It's a conceptually interesting game, and all of the pieces are there. When they work together correctly the game can be a lot of fun. It is unfortunate then, that the game tends to be more a jumbled mess of interesting ideas than a coherent whole.You start out with a few wannabe vampire hunters and begin taking the city back from those bloodsuckers. Combat plays out like plants versus zombies, except your vampire hunters don't have nearly the range or the firepower to really hold their own, even when they have the upgraded weapons. There's a leveling system in place that makes them slightly more formidable but the enemies still seem vastly overpowered.It's also often impossible to tell which lane the enemies are coming down so planning for them all to come from one area and having them all come from the other is soul crushing, especially since moving your soldiers around is unnecessarily hard. The combat isn't terrible, and I did enjoy it when I felt like I had struck the right balance, but that happened far less often than it should have.Let's talk about the cocky piece of crap Dracula. He'll show up basically at any time and screw up your day. This is by far the games most terrible offense. It's basically impossible to kill him with your starting crew, yet he can show up and ♥♥♥♥ up their day within the first few encounters. He'll keep showing up to, and he does considerable damage to your fort if he makes it past your team.Pretty much every time I've lost its because he showed up and wrecked my undergeared soldiers.Healing your soldiers is arduous because they're sent away to the hospital for long periods of time. I could accept that on its own but the amount of time versus the healing done is atrocious in a game where its all about how many men you can field rather than something more tactical like X-Com where a few soldiers CAN pull off the seemingly impossible. Having half your team out of the fight when a big encounter comes up makes you want to throw your keyboard.There's a lot of cool stuff here, but none of it is applied all that well. There are four weapon types, only two of which I found useful. The enemies are cool in concept but vastly overpowered and often times spawning in such great numbers that a full squadron can simply not kill them fast enough. Like I said, I really want to like this game. There are times when I had fun, but I don't think I can reccomend this when there are better alternatives out there.I give it a 5.5/10"
